Key Match Events: The Rockets led by 15 points early before the Knicks got within one late in the fourth quarter. Sengun scored 10 points in the final period to help the Rockets put it away.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Rockets won despite making just 8 of 33 3-pointers. Green started out 0 for 6 and was 2 of 8 and VanVleet and Jabari Smith Jr. each made just 1 of 5 attempts.
Others: The Knicks were outscored 62-38 in the paint as their two-game winning streak was snapped.
